{"TopicId":132594,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Forcing a save (not a quicksave)","CreatedByName":"RocketSquid","CreatedById":152665,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-20T23:33:40Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RocketSquid","CreatedById":152665,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-20T23:33:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI play with a lot of mods, and thus get a lot of crashes. I quicksave often, but quicksaving at non-crucial points can either overwrite my previous, possibly important quicksave, or just make a bunch of new files. Additionally, quickloading often poses some problems of its own. While quicksaving is good for making backups at critical points, it is not to great for making sure your persistent.sfs is up to date. Therefore, I propose a \u0022force save\u0022 feature, that will force an autosave and update the persistent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModerators: please get rid of this thread and PM me if there is already a way to do this, and I\u0027m just to oblivious to realize it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-21T00:19:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/116979-release-automated-screenshots-060-105-compatible/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook beyond the main title of the mod and you will find it does a bit more than just screenshots. Perhaps it fills your need:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003ESpecial Events\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003EThe following are the special events which the mod can sense:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nCrash\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nSpashdown\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nCrew Killed\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nCrwe on eva\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nFlag Planting\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nLaunch\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nPart couple\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nPart die (explode)\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nJoint breaking\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nundocking\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nactivating stage\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nstage seperation\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nchanging vessel\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nmaking orbit\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nescaping orbit\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nSOI changed\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EAutomated Saves\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EThe mod will now do automatic saves at specified intervals. it will only keep a specified number of save files.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nAutomatic saves is turned on by hitting \u003Cstrong\u003ECtrl-F5\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nobodyhasthis2","CreatedById":154685,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-21T00:54:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTotally agree with \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152460\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0022\u003E@swjr-swis\u003C/a\u003E. That what I use for saves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso for heavily modded games. You might also like to avoid unexpected crashing using \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/83821-10x-gcmonitor-127-a-graphic-memory-monitor-july-8th/\u0022\u003EGraphic Memory Monitor\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E. I find it gives a pretty good advanced warning that game is going to crash by hitting the memory cap. This gives\u00A0you a chance to save the game at the\u00A0appropriate time just before a crash happens.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-21T00:57:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222421453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132594\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456011220\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152665\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RocketSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RocketSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut quicksaving at non-crucial points can either overwrite my previous, possibly important quicksave\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt\u002BF5 let\u0027s you create a named quicksave, so you don\u0027t have to overwrite previous saves. This allows you to go back to any point you wish, sort of like keeping your finger between the pages in a \u0022choose your own way\u0022 book.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}